st-qalc: A modification to run qalc in a top-most window (like dmenu), and copy the final calculation result into clipboard.

Extra dependencies: libqalculate, xclip, ansifilter, openssl

Extra keybind: Super + C -> exit the calculator and copy the final result

--------------------
st - simple terminal
--------------------
st is a simple terminal emulator for X which sucks less.


Requirements
------------
In order to build st you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (st is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install st (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running st
----------
If you did not install st with make clean install, you must compile
the st terminfo entry with the following command:

    tic -sx st.info

See the man page for additional details.

Credits
